  "plainText": "Exclusive to:\nCaviar\nFood Info\n12.5\n3\n33\nMeat\nObject Info\n10 Days\nCan be Burned\n40\nCooking Info\nx1 x1 x2\nx3 x1\n40 sec\n20\nMiscellaneous\n\"caviar\"\n“I never had it before I came here.”\n–Wilson\n“Fish eggs in a jar. Great.”\n–Willow\n“Little eggs make Wolfgang feel like big, important man.”\n–Wolfgang\n“I took their life to sustain my own.”\n–Wendy\n“I EXPECTED THEM TO WRIGGLE. DISAPPOINTING”\n–WX-78\n“Differentiated from roe chiefly by the jar.”\n–Wickerbottom\n“Whew, that's salty.”\n–Woodie\n“A meal fitting of my stature.”\n–Maxwell\n“Where did I get that glass jar? Curious...”\n–Wagstaff\n“I wöuld have rathered the fish.”\n–Wigfrid\n“So fancy!”\n–Webber\n“I made them fancy, but they're still fish eggs.”\n–Walani\n“Eat it with a clamshell or the flavor will be ruined.”\n–Warly\n“Snooty landlubb'rin' eats!”\n–Woodlegs\n“YON EGGS HATH THE SQUISHINESS”\n–Wilba\n“Glub Glub babies trapped?”\n–Wormwood\n“If I don't like it, it's going in the Pew-matic.”\n–Wheeler\nCaviar is a Food Item exclusive to the Shipwrecked DLC. It is cooked in the Crock Pot by adding 1 Vegetable and 1 Roe. Alternatively, 3 Cooked Roe can be used.\nCaviar takes 40 seconds to cook, and restores 3 , 12.5 , and 33 when eaten. Due to its low health and hunger restoration, it's best to eat for its high sanity restoration. It can be traded with the Yaarctopus for a Bottle Lantern.\nPrerequisites[edit | edit source]\nRequires:  or\nRequires:\nRecipe[edit | edit source]\n×2\n×3\nExamples[edit | edit source]\n×2\n×2\n×3\n×2\nTrivia[edit | edit source]\nCaviar was added to the Shipwrecked DLC more than a year after its official completion in the Home Sea Home update, after being tested in a beta branch for several months.\nGallery[edit | edit source]\nCaviar as seen in the poster for the Home Sea Home update.\nBy TypeBy Crock Pot Value\nView or edit this template\nFood and Edible Items (by Food Type)\nVeggie\nSeeds\nMeat\nGoodies\nGeneric\nHorrible\nRoughage\nElementals\nBurnt\nRaw\nGears\nGold Dust\nBerry\nWood\nNitre\nLunar Shards\nView or edit this template\nFood and Edible Items (by Food Value)\nMeats\nFishes\nVegetables\nFruits\nMonster Food\nEggs\nDairy\nSweetener\nFrozen\nInedibles\nMagic\nFat\nSeed\nJellyfish\nBone\nFilter\nAntihistamine\nDecoration\nBug\nNo Value Food",
